are and the duration of the X-ray dip is found in our data. In this case the\nX-ray dips prior to ejections could be seen as the time during which the source\naccumulates energy and material that is ejected later.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Dec 2007 09:48:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
